{"title_page": "Sapthagiri College of Engineering, Bangalore", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox college\n| name = Sapthagiri College of Engineering (SCE)\n| image_size = \n| image_alt = \n| caption = \n| latin_name = \n| established = {{start date and age|2001}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sapthagiri.edu.in/|title=Academic Dept|publisher=}}</ref>\n| closed = \n| type = Private\n| chairman = G.Dayanand \n| principal = Dr.H.RAMAKRISHNA\n| dean = \n| city = [[Bangalore]]\n| state = [[Karnataka]]\n| country = India\n| sports = [[Chess]], [[Cricket]], [[Basketball]], [[Throwball]], [[Volleyball]], [[Yoga]]\n| nickname = SCE\n| affiliations = [[Visvesvaraya Technological University]]\n| website = {{URL|https://www.sapthagiri.edu.in/}}\n| footnotes = \n| image_name = Sapthagiri College of Engineering Logo.png\n| colors = \n}}\n\n'''Sapthagiri College of Engineering(SCE)''' is an Engineering college in  [[Bangalore]], [[India]] started in the year 2001.\n\n==About==\nSapthagiri College of Engineering (SCE) is located at Chikkasandra, Hesarghatta Main Road, Bangalore. SCE is affiliated to [[Visvesvaraya Technological University]], [[Belgaum]]<ref>{{cite web |url= http://vtu.ac.in/affiliated-institutes/affiliated-institutes-bengaluru/ |title= Affiliated Institutes - Bengaluru |website= Visvesvaraya Technological University |access-date= 25 June 2017}}</ref> and approved by the [[All India Council for Technical Education]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.aicte-india.org/downloads/ET-15-16/Karnataka_ET.pdf |title= List of Approved Institutes in 2015-16 |website= All India Council for Technical Education |access-date= 25 June 2017}}</ref>\n\nSapthagiri College of Engineering maintains and creates an enabling learning environment for the students. It offers courses such as civil engineering, mechanical engineering, information science & engineering, biotechnology, electrical & electronics engineering, computer science & engineering, and electronics & communications engineering.\n\n==Courses offered==\n===Undergraduate===\n*Biotechnology\n*Civil Engineering\n*Computer Science & Engineering\n*Information Science & Engineering\n*Electronics & Communications Engineering\n*Electrical and Electronics Engineering and\n*Mechanical  Engineering\n\n===Postgraduate===\n*Computer Science & Engineering\n*VLSI design & Embedded system.\n\n===Research centers===\n*Biotechnology\n*Chemistry\n*Physics\n*Computer Science & Engineering\n*Electronics & Communications Engineering\n*Mechanical  Engineering\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://sapthagiri.edu.in}}\n*[http://www.vtu.ac.in Official Website of Visvesvaraya Technological University]\n{{coord|13|4|1.092|N|77|30|11.777|E|type:edu_region:IN-KA|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sapthagiri College Of Engineering, Bangalore}}\n[[Category:Engineering colleges in Bangalore]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2001]]\n[[Category:2001 establishments in India]]\n\n\n\n{{Karnataka-university-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox college\n| name = Sapthagiri College of Engineering (SCE)\n| image_size = \n| image_alt = \n| caption = \n| latin_name = \n| established = {{start date and age|2001}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sapthagiri.edu.in/|title=Academic Dept|publisher=}}</ref>\n| closed = \n| type = Private\n| chairman = G.Dayanand \n| principal = Dr.H.RAMAKRISHNA\n| dean = \n| city = [[Bangalore]]\n| state = [[Karnataka]]\n| country = India\n| sports = [[Chess]], [[Cricket]], [[Basketball]], [[Throwball]], [[Volleyball]], [[Yoga]]\n| nickname = SCE\n| affiliations = [[Visvesvaraya Technological University]]\n| website = {{URL|https://www.sapthagiri.edu.in/}}\n| footnotes = \n| image_name = Sapthagiri College of Engineering Logo.png\n| colors = \n}}\n\n'''Sapthagiri College of Engineering(SCE)''' is an Engineering college in  [[Bangalore]], [[India]] started in the year 2001.\n\n==About==\nSapthagiri College of Engineering (SCE) is located at Chikkasandra, Hesarghatta Main Road, Bangalore. SCE is affiliated to [[Visvesvaraya Technological University]], [[Belgaum]]<ref>{{cite web |url= http://vtu.ac.in/affiliated-institutes/affiliated-institutes-bengaluru/ |title= Affiliated Institutes - Bengaluru |website= Visvesvaraya Technological University |access-date= 25 June 2017}}</ref> and approved by the [[All India Council for Technical Education]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.aicte-india.org/downloads/ET-15-16/Karnataka_ET.pdf |title= List of Approved Institutes in 2015-16 |website= All India Council for Technical Education |access-date= 25 June 2017}}</ref>\n\nSapthagiri College of Engineering maintains and creates an enabling learning environment for the students. It offers courses such as civil engineering, mechanical engineering, information science & engineering, biotechnology, electrical & electronics engineering, computer science & engineering, and electronics & communications engineering.\n\n==Courses offered==\n===Undergraduate===\n*Biotechnology\n*Civil Engineering\n*Computer Science & Engineering\n*Information Science & Engineering\n*Electronics & Communications Engineering\n*Electrical and Electronics Engineering and\n*Mechanical  Engineering\n\n===Postgraduate===\n*Computer Science & Engineering\n*VLSI design & Embedded system.\n\n===Research centers===\n*Biotechnology\n*Chemistry\n*Physics\n*Computer Science & Engineering\n*Electronics & Communications Engineering\n*Mechanical  Engineering\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://sapthagiri.edu.in}}\n*[http://www.vtu.ac.in Official Website of Visvesvaraya Technological University]\n{{coord|13|2|46.55|N|77|30|28.06|E|type:edu_region:IN-KA|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sapthagiri College Of Engineering, Bangalore}}\n[[Category:Engineering colleges in Bangalore]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2001]]\n[[Category:2001 establishments in India]]\n\n\n\n{{Karnataka-university-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Vishwas r", "label": "safe", "comment": "Updated Coordinates", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sapthagiri_College_of_Engineering,_Bangalore"}
{"title_page": "National COVID-19 Coordination Commission", "text_new": "{{use Australian English|date=March 2020}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{confuse|National Cabinet of Australia}}\n{{Infobox Government agency\n|agency_name       = National COVID-19 Coordination Commission\n|type              = Commission\n|seal              = Coat_of_Arms_of_Australia.svg\n|seal_width        = 140px\n|formed            = 25 March 2020\n|preceding1        = \n|jurisdiction      = [[Commonwealth of Australia]]\n|headquarters      = \n|employees         = \n|budget            = \n|image             = \n|chief1_position   = Chair\n|chief1_name       = [[Neville Power]]\n|chief2_position   = Deputy Chair \n|chief2_name       = [[David Thodey]]\n|parent_department = [[Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet (Australia)|Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet]]\n|website           = \n}}\nThe '''National COVID-19 Coordination Commission''' ('''NCCC''') is a strategic advisory body for the national response to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] by the [[Australian Government]].<ref>[https://www.pm.gov.au/media/national-covid-19-coordination-commission National COVID-19 Coordination Commission Media Release] [[Prime Minister's Office (Australia)|Prime Minister's Office]] Media Release 25 March 2020</ref><ref>[https://www.themandarin.com.au/128555-national-covid-coordination-commission-established/ National COVID-19 Coordination Commission established] Shannon Jenkins [[The Mandarin (website)|The Mandarin]] 25 March 2020</ref> The NCCC was established on the 25 March 2020 by [[Prime Minister of Australia|Prime Minister]] Scott Morrison to provide advice on [[Public\u2013private partnership|public-private partnerships]] and coordination to mitigate the social and economic impacts of the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Australia]].<ref>[https://www.afr.com/policy/economy/nev-power-to-lead-covid-19-commission-20200325-p54duh Nev Power to lead COVID-19 commission] Julie-anne Sprague [[Australian Financial Review]] 25 March 2020</ref><ref>[https://www.smh.com.au/politics/federal/morrison-launches-covid-19-coordination-commission-cancels-non-urgent-surgery-20200325-p54dpx.html Morrison launches COVID-19 Coordination Commission, cancels non-urgent surgery] Dana McCauley [[Sydney Morning Herald]] 25 March 2020</ref>\n\n==Executive Board membership==\nPrime Minister [[Scott Morrison]] announced the membership of the Executive Board of the NCCC to consist of leaders from the private and public sectors.<ref>[https://www.pmc.gov.au/news-centre/domestic-policy/announcement-national-covid-19-coordination-commission-nccc Announcement of the National COVID-19 Coordination Commission (NCCC)] [[Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet (Australia)|Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet]] News Story 25 March 2020</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Position\n!Office holder\n!Background\n|-\n|Chair\n|[[Neville Power]]\n|Former CEO of [[Fortescue Metals Group]]\n|-\n|Deputy Chair\n|[[David Thodey]] [[Officer of the Order of Australia|AO]]\n|Chair of the [[CSIRO]] and former CEO of [[Telstra]]\n|-\n|Commissioner\n|[[Greg Combet]] [[Member of the Order of Australia|AM]]\n|Former [[Australian Labor Party]] [[Minister for Industry, Science and Technology|Minister for Industry and Innovation]]\n|-\n|Commissioner\n|[[Jane Halton]] [[Officer of the Order of Australia|AO]] [[Public Service Medal (Australia)|PSM]]\n|Former Secretary of the [[Department of Finance (Australia)|Department of Finance]] and the [[Department of Health (Australia)|Department of Health]]\n|-\n|Commissioner\n|[[Paul Little (Australian businessman)|Paul Little]]\n|Former Managing Director of [[Toll Group]]\n|-\n|Commissioner\n|Catherine Tanna\n|Managing Director of [[EnergyAustralia]]\n|-\n|Commissioner\n|[[Philip Gaetjens]]\n|Secretary of the [[Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet (Australia)|Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet]]\n|-\n|Commissioner\n|[[Mike Pezzullo]]\n|Secretary of the [[Department of Home Affairs (Australia)|Department of Home Affairs]]\n|}\n\n==Secretariat==\nThe [[Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet (Australia)|Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet]] provides secretariat support functions for the NCCC.\n\n==See also==\n* [[Australian Health Protection Principal Committee]]\n* [[National Cabinet of Australia]]\n* [[Council of Australian Governments]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Government of Australia]]\n[[Category:Public policy in Australia]]\n[[Category:2020 in Australia]]\n", "text_old": "{{use Australian English|date=March 2020}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{confuse|National Cabinet of Australia}}\n{{Infobox Government agency\n|agency_name       = National COVID-19 Coordination Commission\n|type              = Commission\n|seal              = Coat_of_Arms_of_Australia.svg\n|seal_width        = 140px\n|formed            = 25 March 2020\n|preceding1        = \n|jurisdiction      = [[Commonwealth of Australia]]\n|headquarters      = \n|employees         = \n|budget            = \n|image             = \n|chief1_position   = Chair\n|chief1_name       = [[Neville Power]]\n|chief2_position   = Deputy Chair \n|chief2_name       = [[David Thodey]]\n|parent_department = [[Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet (Australia)|Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet]]\n|website           = \n}}\nThe '''National COVID-19 Coordination Commission''' ('''NCCC''') is a strategic advisory body for the national response to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] by the [[Australian Government]].<ref>[https://www.pm.gov.au/media/national-covid-19-coordination-commission National COVID-19 Coordination Commission Media Release] [[Prime Minister's Office (Australia)|Prime Minister's Office]] Media Release 25 March 2020</ref><ref>[https://www.themandarin.com.au/128555-national-covid-coordination-commission-established/ National COVID-19 Coordination Commission established] Shannon Jenkins [[The Mandarin (website)|The Mandarin]] 25 March 2020</ref> The NCCC was established on the 25 March 2020 by Prime Minister Scott Morrison to provide advice on [[Public\u2013private partnership|public-private partnerships]] and coordination to mitigate the social and economic impacts of the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Australia]].<ref>[https://www.afr.com/policy/economy/nev-power-to-lead-covid-19-commission-20200325-p54duh Nev Power to lead COVID-19 commission] Julie-anne Sprague [[Australian Financial Review]] 25 March 2020</ref><ref>[https://www.smh.com.au/politics/federal/morrison-launches-covid-19-coordination-commission-cancels-non-urgent-surgery-20200325-p54dpx.html Morrison launches COVID-19 Coordination Commission, cancels non-urgent surgery] Dana McCauley [[Sydney Morning Herald]] 25 March 2020</ref>\n\n==Executive Board membership==\nPrime Minister [[Scott Morrison]] announced the membership of the Executive Board of the NCCC to consist of leaders from the private and public sectors.<ref>[https://www.pmc.gov.au/news-centre/domestic-policy/announcement-national-covid-19-coordination-commission-nccc Announcement of the National COVID-19 Coordination Commission (NCCC)] [[Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet (Australia)|Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet]] News Story 25 March 2020</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Position\n!Office holder\n!Background\n|-\n|Chair\n|[[Neville Power]]\n|Former CEO of [[Fortescue Metals Group]]\n|-\n|Deputy Chair\n|[[David Thodey]] [[Officer of the Order of Australia|AO]]\n|Chair of the [[CSIRO]] and former CEO of [[Telstra]]\n|-\n|Commissioner\n|[[Greg Combet]] [[Member of the Order of Australia|AM]]\n|Former [[Australian Labor Party]] [[Minister for Industry, Science and Technology|Minister for Industry and Innovation]]\n|-\n|Commissioner\n|[[Jane Halton]] [[Officer of the Order of Australia|AO]] [[Public Service Medal (Australia)|PSM]]\n|Former Secretary of the [[Department o