{"title_page": "Joyce Bennett", "text_new": "{{unsourced|date=October 2019}} \n{{For|the Anglican priest|Joyce M. Bennett}}\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.womenaustralia.info/biogs/AWE2546b.htm|title=Bennett, Joyce - Woman - The Australian Women's Register|last=Melbourne|first=National Foundation for Australian Women and The University of|website=www.womenaustralia.info|language=en-gb|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=September 2016}}\n\n'''Joyce Bennett''' (Sala Tenna) (born 11 May 1945 in [[Guildford, Western Australia]]) is a former [[Australia]]n [[Sprint (running)|sprint]]er.\n\nAt the [[Athletics at the 1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games|1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games]] in Perth she won silver in the 220 Yards and gold in the 4 \u00d7 110 yards relay. Four years later at the [[Athletics at the 1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games|1966 British Empire and Commonwealth Games]] in Kingston she defended her title in the 4 \u00d7 110 yards relay.\n\nShe participated in the 1964 Summer Olympics ([[Athletics at the 1964 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 200 metres|half-final in the 200 m]], [[Athletics at the 1964 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 4 \u00d7 100 metres relay|sixth in the 4 \u00d7 100 metres relay]]) and in the 1968 Summer Olympics ([[Athletics at the 1968 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 400 metres|heat in the 400 m]], [[Athletics at the 1968 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 4 \u00d7 100 metres relay|fifth in the 4 \u00d7 100 metres relay]]).\nShe won first in many other events too\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://athletics.possumbility.com/athletes/athlete109.htm Joyce Bennett] at Australian Athletics Historical Results\n* [http://trackfield.brinkster.net/Profile.asp?ID=182&Gender=W Joyce Bennett] at ''trackfield.brinkster.net''\n* {{SR/Olympics|be/joyce-bennett-1}}\n\n{{Footer Australia NC 100m Women}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bennett, Joyce}}\n[[Category:1945 births]]\n[[Category:Australian female sprinters]]\n[[Category:Olympic athletes of Australia]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1964 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1968 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1966 British Empire and Commonwealth Games]]\n[[Category:Commonwealth Games silver medallists for Australia]]\n[[Category:Commonwealth Games gold medallists for Australia]]\n[[Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in athletics]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n\n\n{{Australia-athletics-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{unsourced|date=October 2019}} \n{{For|the Anglican priest|Joyce M. Bennett}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=September 2016}}\n\n'''Joyce Bennett''' (Sala Tenna) (born 11 May 1945 in [[Guildford, Western Australia]]) is a former [[Australia]]n [[Sprint (running)|sprint]]er.\n\nAt the [[Athletics at the 1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games|1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games]] in Perth she won silver in the 220 Yards and gold in the 4 \u00d7 110 yards relay. Four years later at the [[Athletics at the 1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games|1966 British Empire and Commonwealth Games]] in Kingston she defended her title in the 4 \u00d7 110 yards relay.\n\nShe participated in the 1964 Summer Olympics ([[Athletics at the 1964 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 200 metres|half-final in the 200 m]], [[Athletics at the 1964 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 4 \u00d7 100 metres relay|sixth in the 4 \u00d7 100 metres relay]]) and in the 1968 Summer Olympics ([[Athletics at the 1968 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 400 metres|heat in the 400 m]], [[Athletics at the 1968 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 4 \u00d7 100 metres relay|fifth in the 4 \u00d7 100 metres relay]]).\nShe won first in many other events too\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://athletics.possumbility.com/athletes/athlete109.htm Joyce Bennett] at Australian Athletics Historical Results\n* [http://trackfield.brinkster.net/Profile.asp?ID=182&Gender=W Joyce Bennett] at ''trackfield.brinkster.net''\n* {{SR/Olympics|be/joyce-bennett-1}}\n\n{{Footer Australia NC 100m Women}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bennett, Joyce}}\n[[Category:1945 births]]\n[[Category:Australian female sprinters]]\n[[Category:Olympic athletes of Australia]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1964 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1968 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1966 British Empire and Commonwealth Games]]\n[[Category:Commonwealth Games silver medallists for Australia]]\n[[Category:Commonwealth Games gold medallists for Australia]]\n[[Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in athletics]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n\n\n{{Australia-athletics-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "GeorgeZhuu", "label": "safe", "comment": "add a refference", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joyce_Bennett"}
{"title_page": "Menlo Park, California", "text_new": "{{other uses of|Menlo Park}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!--See the table at Template:Infobox settlement for all fields and descriptions of their usage.-->\n<!-- Basic info  ---------------->\n| name                            = Menlo Park\n| official_name                   = City of Menlo Park\n| settlement_type                 = [[City (California)|City]]\n| nickname                        = \n| motto                           = <!-- images and maps  ----------->\n| image_skyline                   = Downtown Menlo Park California.jpg\n| image_caption                   = Downtown Menlo Park\n| image_flag                      = \n| flag_size                       = \n| image_seal                      = \n| seal_size                       = \n| image_blank_emblem              = Menlo Park California Logo.gif\n| image_map                       = San_Mateo_County_California_Incorporated_and_Unincorporated_areas_Menlo_Park_Highlighted.svg\n| mapsize                         = 250x200px\n| map_caption                     = Location in [[San Mateo County, California|San Mateo County]] and the state of California\n| pushpin_map                     = USA California#USA\n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in California##Location in the United States\n| pushpin_relief                  = 1\n| image_map1                      = Menlo Park street map plan California USA.svg\n| mapsize1                        = 250px\n| map_caption1                    = Menlo Park street map, California\n<!-- Location ------------------>\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = {{USA}}\n| subdivision_type1               = State\n| subdivision_name1               = {{flag|California}}\n| subdivision_type2               = [[List of counties in California|County]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[San Mateo County, California|San Mateo]]\n<!-- Politics --------